'From Squeak2.8alpha of 4 February 2000 [latest update: #2098] on 12 May 2000 at 10:41:22 am'!"Change Set:		053SketchEditorEnh-kfrDate:			10 May 2000Author:			Karl RambergHere is a change set that changes the way the sketchEditorMorph draws a dim image behind it self. The method used before this change set was probably made before the translucentColors were introduced."!!MappedCollection methodsFor: 'printing' stamp: 'sma 5/11/2000 19:53'!storeOn: aStream	aStream		nextPut: $(;		nextPutAll: self class name;		nextPutAll: ' collection: ';		store: domain;		nextPutAll: ' map: ';		store: map;		nextPut: $)! !!SketchEditorMorph methodsFor: 'palette handling' stamp: 'kfr 5/10/2000 13:42'!dimTheWindow	"Updated to use TranslucentColor by kfr 10/5 00"	"Do not call twice!! Installs a morph with an 'onion-skinned' copy of the pixels behind me." 		"create an 'onion-skinned' version of the stuff on the screen"	owner outermostMorphThat: [:morph | morph resumeAfterDrawError. false].	dimForm _ (RectangleMorph new color: (TranslucentColor r:1.0 g:1.0 b:1.0 alpha:0.5) ; bounds: self bounds; borderWidth: 0).	dimForm position: self position.	owner		privateAddMorph: dimForm		atIndex: (owner submorphs indexOf: self) + 1.! !